# These patterns catch accidental drops; move violators OUT manually.
genesis_*_audit*.md
genesis_master_plan*.md
genesis_improvement_plan*.md
genesis_runtime_*.md
genesis_local_*.md
genesis_deep_*.md
genesis_project_*.md
github_research*.md
grok_*.md
todos-log-*.md
.README_*backup*.md
.README_v*_backup*.md

# ─── Commercial engine package boundary (defense-in-depth) ───────────
# `vllm/sndr_engine/` is the COMMERCIAL package namespace. It lives
# inside the `vllm/` import path (cannot be moved into sndr_private/
# without breaking Python imports), so it gets its own gitignore rule.
# Primary boundary: a real release moves sndr_engine to a SEPARATE
# private repo. This rule is the safety net against accidental
# `git add .` on a development checkout.
vllm/sndr_engine/

# Audit / plan files at repo root (also catches sndr_*_audit_*.md)
sndr_*_audit_*.md
sndr_*_plan_*.md
sndr_repeat_*.md

